                <h1 id="the-cosmic-framework-divine-abyssal-and-parasitic-realms">The Cosmic Framework: Divine, Abyssal, and Parasitic Realms</h1>
<figure style="text-align: center; margin: 1em 0;">
    <img src="/static/cosmology_overview_diagram.svg" alt="A diagram of the cosmic framework, showing the Sefirotic Tree of Life, the Abyss of Da'at, and the inverted Qliphothic Tree of Death." style="max-width: 500px; height: auto; border-radius: 4px; border: 1px solid #444;">
    <figcaption style="font-style: italic; color: #888;">The three major realms of existence.</figcaption>
</figure>

<h2 id="the-divine-flow">The Divine Flow</h2>
<p>All reality emanates from the <strong>Ein Sof</strong>, the endless, unknowable source. The raw energy of the Ein Sof is too vast for mortals to bear. The ten <a href="/w/magic-system/glossary#sefirah-pl-sefirot"><strong>Sefirot</strong></a> act as cosmic filters, stepping down this infinite power into ten distinct, usable concepts.</p>
<p>Between the Supernal Triad (S1, S2, S3) and the lower seven Sefirot lies a conceptual void known as <strong>The Abyss</strong>. At its center is <a href="/w/world-lore/cosmology/daat-the-abyss"><strong>Da'at</strong></a>, a wound in reality. While the Sefirot are pathways of Being, Da'at is a conduit to Non-Being, and to touch it is to risk utter erasure.</p>
<h2 id="the-worlds-shadow-the-qliphoth">The World's Shadow: The Qliphoth</h2>
<p>If the Sefirot are divine principles, the <a href="/w/world-lore/cosmology/the-qliphoth"><strong>Qliphoth</strong></a> (lit. "Husks") are their cancerous shadows. They are not an opposite force, but the horrifying extreme of a Sefirah's concept taken to its absolute limit, divorced from any balancing influence.</p>
<p>To draw power from these Husks is to invite <a href="/w/magic-system/core-mechanics/corruption#5-infestation"><strong>Infestation</strong></a>—a spiritual parasite that consumes the soul, twisting a mage into a monstrous <strong>Avatar</strong>.</p>
<p>(For a detailed catalogue of the Husks, see <a href="/w/world-lore/cosmology/the-qliphoth">The Qliphoth</a>.)</p>
            </main>

            

